<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
United States, Mexico (Baja California; Chiapas, new state record; Guanajuato; Oaxaca), Guatemala (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.2001.00144.x" author="Miller, KB" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="87 - 123" refId="B61" refString="Miller, KB, 2001. Revision and phylogenetic analysis of the New World genus Neoclypeodytes Young (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae: Hydroporinae: Bidessini). Systematic Entomology 26: 87 - 123, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.2001.00144.x" title="Revision and phylogenetic analysis of the New World genus Neoclypeodytes Young (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae: Hydroporinae: Bidessini)." url="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.2001.00144.x" volume="26" year="2001">Miller 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Dugesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" publicationUrl="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" refId="B75" refString="Nilsson, AN, Hajek, J, 2020. A World Catalogue of the Family Dytiscidae, or the Diving Beetles (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Version 1.I.2020. National Museum, Prague. http://www.waterbeetles.eu" title="A World Catalogue of the Family Dytiscidae, or the Diving Beetles (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Version 1. I. 2020. National Museum, Prague." url="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" year="2020">
Nilsson and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hájek">Hajek</normalizedToken>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). This species was previously recorded at an altitudinal range between 853 and 1,524 m (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.2001.00144.x" author="Miller, KB" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="87 - 123" refId="B61" refString="Miller, KB, 2001. Revision and phylogenetic analysis of the New World genus Neoclypeodytes Young (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae: Hydroporinae: Bidessini). Systematic Entomology 26: 87 - 123, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.2001.00144.x" title="Revision and phylogenetic analysis of the New World genus Neoclypeodytes Young (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae: Hydroporinae: Bidessini)." url="https://doi.org/10.1046/j.1365-3113.2001.00144.x" volume="26" year="2001">Miller 2001</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, the species was collected at level 4 (rivers 1 and 2, 1,425-1,619 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
